summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions on CÃ´te d'Ivoire, 

Authorizes the deployment of an additional 2,000 military personnel to UNOCI until 30 June 2011; 

Authorizes the extension until 30 June 2011 of temporary additional military and police capabilities; 

Authorizes the Secretary-General to extend by up to four weeks the temporary redeployment from UNMIL to UNOCI of three infantry companies and one aviation unit; 

Authorizes the transfer of three armed helicopters with crews from UNMIL to UNOCI for a period of four weeks; 

Authorizes the deployment of 60 formed police unit personnel; 

Requests the Secretary-General to review temporary personnel deployments by 31 March 2011; 

Authorizes immediate deployment of additional capacities and requests troop- and police-contributing countries' support; 

Reiterates authorization and full support for the Special Representative to carry out UNOCI's mandate; 

Demands all parties respect UNOCI's safety and freedom of movement; 

Demands an immediate halt to using media to propagate false information and incite hatred and violence; 

 Reiterates readiness to impose measures, including targeted sanctions, against those obstructing UNOCI's work; 

Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
